<chapter>
  <title id="edpykota">Maintaining the Print Quota DataBase with edpykota</title>
  <para>Last modified on $Date$</para>
  
  <para>
    <application>edpykota</application> is the command line tool with which you will 
    maintain your print quota database.
  </para>
  
  <para>
    Here's a list of features :
    
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Add printers ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Add and delete users and groups ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Set users' account balances ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Set users and groups print quotas on printers, eventually by using another user
          or group as a template ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Set price per page and price per job for printers ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Switch users or groups to <quote>account only</quote> mode (no quota enforcement) ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Define hard and soft limits for users ou groups quotas, on a per printer basis ;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Choose the way you will limit printing : either by page quota or by account balance value.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
  
</chapter>

